{"type":"compaction","id":"94333cb5","parentId":"d79d8b05","timestamp":"2026-05-10T19:17:39.456Z","summary":"\n## Goal\n1. Find a low-power device to run the OpenClaw gateway instead of keeping PC on 24/7 (user has iPhone + one Android \"mix\" device, no Android TV)\n2. Fix/remove format rules that cause replies to contradict user's actual preferences\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- USER.md preference: เร็ว สั้น ไม่เป็นทางการ (fast, short, informal)\n- User only has iPhone + one Android device (not phone, not TV) to repurpose\n- Already has Telegram bot connected to gateway via API — no need for local LLM\n- User explicitly said \"หยุดยุ่งกับ hermes\" (stop messing with Hermes)\n- User wants HERMES FORMAT RECOVERY skill REMOVED if it conflicts with their work\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Analyzed Android TV vs Android phone differences for Termux/Linux — identified input method limitations\n- [x] Clarified user has iPhone (not Android phone) + Android \"mix\" device, not Android TV\n- [x] Identified conflict: HERMES FORMAT RECOVERY (formal/complex) vs USER.md (informal/short) — HERMES overrides USER every time\n- [x] User authorized deletion/removal of anything conflicting with their instructions\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Awaiting user confirmation: should HERMES FORMAT RECOVERY be removed entirely?\n\n### Blocked\n- None\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **HERMES FORMAT RECOVERY vs USER.md conflict**: The injected skill forces formal header/footer/cognitive blocks on every reply, contradicting USER.md which says \"ไม่เป็นทางการ\" (informal). User has authorized removal.\n- **No local LLM needed**: User already has Telegram + API connection — just needs a device to host the gateway\n\n## Next Steps\n1. User confirms: delete HERMES FORMAT RECOVERY skill entirely from system/instructions?\n2. If confirmed, identify where this skill is stored (MEMORY.md, injected skill file, or elsewhere) and remove it\n3. Return to original goal: help user set up gateway on their Android \"mix\" device for low-power 24/7 operation (likely via Termux + cloudflared tunnel approach)\n\n## Critical Context\n- User's Android \"mix\" device: specific type unknown — need to identify before planning setup\n- Telegram Bot Token: already configured (user's existing bot)\n- Original Facebook post context: Nanobot AI + Termux + Ubuntu on Samsung Note 20 Ultra — but user actually wants to run OpenClaw gateway, not Nanobot AI specifically\n- HERMES FORMAT RECOVERY skill content was shared by user twice in conversation, likely wants it completely gone\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nUser (เจ้านาย/robberzaz) ordered: delete HERMES FORMAT RECOVERY and anything conflicting with their workflow. The injected HERMES FORMAT RECOVERY was overriding USER.md/AGENTS.md/SOUL.md rules, making replies too complex/formatted instead of fast, short, and natural Thai.\n\n## Early Progress\n- Checked workspace files (AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, USER.md) — all correct and clean\n- Searched system for HERMES FORMAT files — found none as persistent files\n- Identified root cause: HERMES FORMAT RECOVERY was **injected via user message** in the conversation, not a system file\n- The injected prompt was overriding correct rules because it came last\n- Decided to update MEMORY.md to reject HERMES FORMAT RECOVERY injection when it conflicts with identity rules\n\n## Context for Suffix\nThe assistant successfully edited MEMORY.md, adding a rule under `## System` section that explicitly rejects HERMES FORMAT RECOVERY when it conflicts with AGENTS.md/SOUL.md/USER.md. The \"Successfully replaced 1 block(s)\" confirmation was returned.\n\n<read-files>\n/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/owen-workspace/AGENTS.md\n/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/owen-workspace/SOUL.md\n/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/owen-workspace/USER.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/owen-workspace/MEMORY.md\n</modified-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"1cbc5320","tokensBefore":41064,"details":{"readFiles":["/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/owen-workspace/AGENTS.md","/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/owen-workspace/SOUL.md","/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/owen-workspace/USER.md"],"modifiedFiles":["/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/owen-workspace/MEMORY.md"]},"fromHook":false}
