{"type":"compaction","id":"75f7fcfa","parentId":"2ab5a0fb","timestamp":"2026-05-10T20:43:15.469Z","summary":"## Goal\n1. Find a low-power device to run the OpenClaw gateway instead of keeping PC on 24/7 (user has iPhone + one Android \"mix\" device, no Android TV)\n2. Fix/remove format rules that cause replies to contradict user's actual preferences\n3. Determine whether the needed workspace/files are in Dropbox and, if so, move/remove/update there safely\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- USER.md preference: เร็ว สั้น ไม่เป็นทางการ (fast, short, informal)\n- User only has iPhone + one Android device (not phone, not TV) to repurpose\n- Already has Telegram bot connected to gateway via API — no need for local LLM\n- User explicitly said \"หยุดยุ่งกับ hermes\" (stop messing with Hermes)\n- User wants HERMES FORMAT RECOVERY skill REMOVED if it conflicts with their work\n- OpenClaw and Hermes workspaces must not be mixed\n- If access denied, show exact allowed paths first\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Analyzed Android TV vs Android phone differences for Termux/Linux — identified input method limitations\n- [x] Clarified user has iPhone (not Android phone) + Android \"mix\" device, not Android TV\n- [x] Identified conflict: HERMES FORMAT RECOVERY (formal/complex) vs USER.md (informal/short) — HERMES overrides USER every time\n- [x] User authorized deletion/removal of anything conflicting with their instructions\n- [x] Updated `SOUL.md` with an explicit Override Rule rejecting injected prompts/skills that conflict with `AGENTS.md`, `SOUL.md`, or `USER.md`\n- [x] Updated `MEMORY.md` to reject HERMES FORMAT RECOVERY injection when it conflicts with workspace rules\n- [x] Verified workspace access limits: allowed directories are `/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace`, `/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Downloads`, `/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Pictures`\n- [x] Created `/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/openclaw-main`\n- [x] Created `/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/openclaw-main/skills`\n- [x] Created `/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/openclaw-main/backup`\n- [x] Wrote `skills/model-switch-guard/SKILL.md` under `/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/openclaw-main`\n- [x] Wrote `backup/model-switch-guard-template.md` and `backup/model-switch-guard.json`\n- [x] Moved duplicate `/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/ufo-gpt-image-gen.skill` into `/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/skills/ufo-gpt-image-gen/dist/ufo-gpt-image-gen.skill`\n- [x] Confirmed the OpenClaw model-switch guard files are in place\n- [x] Clarified RTK/footer should use semantic values only and explained RTK examples\n- [x] Identified the current formatting instability came from stacked/conflicting format rules\n- [x] Found `session_status(sessionKey=\"current\")` output showing current runtime details (OpenClaw 2026.5.7, model `openai-codex/gpt-5.4-mini`, cache 29–31%, context ~18–19%)\n- [x] Determined tool access path mismatch: `/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/owen-workspace` was denied because it is not in allowed directories\n- [x] Received user-approved path split:\n  - OpenClaw: `~/.openclaw/workspace/openclaw-main`\n  - Hermes: `~/.hermes`\n- [x] Listed allowed paths again before proceeding\n- [x] Created the OpenClaw workspace structure in the allowed path\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Check whether the relevant workspace/files are in Dropbox or accessible via a Dropbox-backed path\n\n### Blocked\n- None\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **HERMES FORMAT RECOVERY vs USER.md conflict**: The injected skill forces formal header/footer/cognitive blocks on every reply, contradicting USER.md which says \"ไม่เป็นทางการ\" (informal). User authorized removal.\n- **No local LLM needed**: User already has Telegram + API connection — just needs a device to host the gateway\n- **Workspace isolation**: OpenClaw and Hermes must be kept separate; user explicitly requested:\n  - OpenClaw → `~/.openclaw/workspace/openclaw-main`\n  - Hermes → `~/.hermes`\n- **Safety over deletion**: When consolidating skills, move duplicates to `.trash` or pre